---
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Best Cable Management for Desk 2026';
const pageDescription = 'Honest review of cable management boxes and cord organizers. Hide power strips and eliminate desk clutter in under 10 minutes.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #333; }
      h1 { color: #232f3e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
      .meta { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
      .product-box { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
      .product-box h2 { margin-top: 0; }
      .product-box ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
      .btn { display: inline-block; background: #ff9900; color: #000; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
      .btn:hover { background: #e68a00; }
      .disclaimer { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #888; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 1rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Cable Management for Desk</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated May 2026 · Under $25</div>

      <p>You bought the monitor, the hub, the charging stand, and the lamp. Now your desk looks like a spaghetti factory. A cable management box hides the power strip and adapters, while adhesive clips route wires along the back edge of your desk. The result is a surface so clean it looks like a showroom.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>🏆 Cable Management Box with Cord Clips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Large capacity box</strong> — fits power strips up to 13" long, 5" wide</li>
          <li><strong>Ventilated lid</strong> — prevents heat buildup from chargers</li>
          <li><strong>10 adhesive cable clips</strong> — route wires along desk legs and back edge</li>
          <li><strong>Bamboo lid option</strong> — matches wood desks, doubles as a mini shelf</li>
          <li><strong>Tool-free install</strong> — peel, stick, and hide cables in 5 minutes</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=cable+management+box+desk&tag=toolwise20-20" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Check Current Price on Amazon</a>
      </div>

      <h3>Why a box beats zip ties</h3>
      <p>Zip ties look tidy for one day, then you need to swap a cable and end up cutting them all off. A management box lets you add or remove plugs in seconds. The adhesive clips keep individual cords from dangling, which is the real secret to a clean desk — not hiding the power strip, but controlling the last 12 inches of every wire.</p>

      <h3>Who should buy it</h3>
      <p>Anyone who owns a USB-C hub, wireless charger, monitor light bar, or laptop stand — which is exactly the setup we have been building across our previous reviews. If you followed our recommendations for a portable monitor, mechanical keyboard, and noise-canceling headphones, this is the final piece that makes the entire desk look intentional instead of improvised.</p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        Disclosure: As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This review is based on independent research and reader feedback.
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>